bstring
------------------------------------------
This is a fork of Paul Hsiehs Better String Library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.2-1
  libbstring-devel-1.0.0-1bl2
  libbstring0-1.0.0-1bl2
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.37-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-8
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/msteinert/bstring

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/msteinert/bstring/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bstring-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bstring-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bstring-1.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bstring-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbstring0-1.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbstring-devel-1.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bstring)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bstring.README
  /usr/share/doc/bstring/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/bstring/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/bstring/comparisons.md
  /usr/share/doc/bstring/introduction.md
  /usr/share/doc/bstring/porting.md
  /usr/share/doc/bstring/security.md

(libbstring0)
  /usr/bin/cygbstring-0.dll

(libbstring-devel)
  /usr/include/bstring/bstraux.h
  /usr/include/bstring/bstrlib.h
  /usr/lib/libbstring.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/bstring.pc

------------------

